methods.calc:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**

Finds the minimum and maximum of the data in the column of the table and splits this range into
 nbins equally sized bins. Calculates the number of data values in each bin.
 
 Data which is not normal as defined in DoubleFpPrimitives.isNormal(double) is filtered out of the data set.

*Overload 1*  
  :param table: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) - table
  :param column: (java.lang.String) - column in table
  :param nbins: (int) - number of bins
  :param plotInfo: (io.deephaven.plot.errors.PlotInfo) - plot information
  :param byColumns: (java.lang.String...) - other columns needed to calaculate histogram, these columns will be included while grouping
  :return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) table holding the calculated bins and their counts
  
*Overload 2*

  :param byColumns: (java.util.List<java.lang.String>) - other columns needed to calaculate histogram, these columns will be included while grouping
  :return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) table holding the calculated bins and their counts
  
*Overload 3*

  :param rangeMax: (double) - range maximum
  :param nbins: (int) - number of bins

  :param byColumns: (java.lang.String...) - other columns needed to calaculate histogram, these columns will be included while grouping
  :return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) table holding the calculated bins and their counts

text: Utility for calculating histogram plot information: bin locations and data frequencies within these bins.
